Description: official Python client for the OpenAI API (Avalan PPA pin)
 The openai SDK exposes typed Python bindings for the OpenAI REST API
 plus sync and async clients backed by httpx, streaming helpers, and
 tool-call utilities. Avalan ships it in its `vendors` extra at
 `>= 2.0, < 3`; Debian sid carries 2.21.x but its source Build-Depends
 on Noble-missing transitive deps, so the rebuild pins the upstream
 PyPI sdist instead.
 .
 The optional `jiter` Rust accelerator is intentionally not declared
 as a Depends. The streaming chat-completion helper imports
 `from_json` at module-load time, so the upstream import is rewritten
 to pull `from_json` from `pydantic_core` (already in this PPA), which
 ships the same API. The HTTP / completion paths Avalan exercises do
 not need jiter to function.
